    "Unknown": "His miracles, Isa_35:5,\n4. In civil things parents have a great power, during the nonage of children, and after also in matters which concern their parents \u2018 good , as to command them to assist them, to help to supply their necessities, &c.\n4. God doth what he stirs up his servants to do; it was Nebuchchadnezzar who was appointed to do this, and who did it, [v_Jer_27_6] as #Jer 27:6 28:",
    "Exodus & Leviticus": "And Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` spake unto all the congregation of the children of\nIsrael, etc.] Continued his speech to them, being convened by him, after by\nway of preface he had repeated the law of the sabbath, with an additional\ncircumstance to it, \u201cpro tempore\u201d:\nsaying, this is the thing which the Lord commanded; ordered Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` to\ninform them of as his will, when he was with him upon the mount the first\ntime; but through their idolatry, and time spent in making up matters\nbetween God and them, he had not had till now an opportunity of\nacquainting them with it:\nsaying; as follows."
